        "accordion_item_tmnRC9": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is dry mouth?",
            "content": "<div itemprop=\"text\">\n                        \n<p><a href=\"https://www.mayoclinic.org/diseases-conditions/dry-mouth/symptoms-causes/syc-20356048\" onclick=\"javascript:window.open('https://www.mayoclinic.org/diseases-conditions/dry-mouth/symptoms-causes/syc-20356048', '_blank', 'noopener'); return false;\" data-uw-rm-brl=\"PR\" data-uw-original-href=\"https://www.mayoclinic.org/diseases-conditions/dry-mouth/symptoms-causes/syc-20356048\">Dry mouth</a>, also known as xerostomia, is pretty much just what it sounds like. If you’ve experienced your mouth feeling excessively dry (where you can’t seem to make enough saliva to keep it moistened), you’re likely familiar with dry mouth. It can make talking or swallowing a challenge, and your mouth will probably feel sticky. You might also notice that the saliva you do produce feels thick and stringy. Dry mouth isn’t just a matter of discomfort or inconvenience — it can also lead to health issues such as tooth decay and gingivitis, as well as bad breath.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re wondering, “What is cottonmouth?” <a href=\"/articles/blog/cottonmouth-signs-symptoms/\" data-uw-rm-brl=\"PR\" data-uw-original-href=\"/articles/blog/cottonmouth-signs-symptoms/\">the answer is no different</a>; it’s just another name for the same issue.</p>\n<div class=\"swp-hidden-panel-wrap\" style=\"display: none; visibility: collapse; opacity: 0\"><div class=\"swp_social_panel swp_horizontal_panel swp_flat_fresh  swp_default_full_color swp_individual_full_color swp_other_full_color scale-100  scale-\" data-min-width=\"1100\" data-float-color=\"#ffffff\" data-float=\"none\" data-float-mobile=\"none\" data-transition=\"slide\" data-post-id=\"14205\">\n<div class=\"nc_tweetContainer swp_share_button swp_twitter\" data-network=\"twitter\"><a class=\"nc_tweet swp_share_link\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=What+is+dry+mouth%3F&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smartmouth.com%2Ffaqs%2Fwhat-is-dry-mouth%2F\" data-link=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=What+is+dry+mouth%3F&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smartmouth.com%2Ffaqs%2Fwhat-is-dry-mouth%2F\" data-uw-rm-brl=\"PR\" data-uw-original-href=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=What+is+dry+mouth%3F&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smartmouth.com%2Ffaqs%2Fwhat-is-dry-mouth%2F\" aria-label=\"twitter - open in a new tab\" data-uw-rm-empty-ctrl=\"\" data-uw-rm-ext-link=\"\" uw-rm-external-link-id=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=what+is+dry+mouth%3f&amp;url=https%3a%2f%2fwww.smartmouth.com%2ffaqs%2fwhat-is-dry-mouth%2f$twitter\"><span class=\"swp_count swp_hide\"><span class=\"iconFiller\"><span class=\"spaceManWilly\"><i class=\"sw swp_twitter_icon\"></i><span class=\"swp_share\">Tweet</span></span></span></span></a></div>\n<div class=\"nc_tweetContainer swp_share_button swp_linkedin\" data-network=\"linkedin\"><a class=\"nc_tweet swp_share_link\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/cws/share?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smartmouth.com%2Ffaqs%2Fwhat-is-dry-mouth%2F\" data-link=\"https://www.linkedin.com/cws/share?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smartmouth.com%2Ffaqs%2Fwhat-is-dry-mouth%2F\" aria-label=\"linkedin - open in a new tab\" data-uw-rm-empty-ctrl=\"\" data-uw-rm-ext-link=\"\" uw-rm-external-link-id=\"https://www.linkedin.com/cws/share?url=https%3a%2f%2fwww.smartmouth.com%2ffaqs%2fwhat-is-dry-mouth%2f$linkedin\"><span class=\"swp_count swp_hide\"><span class=\"iconFiller\"><span class=\"spaceManWilly\"><i class=\"sw swp_linkedin_icon\"></i><span class=\"swp_share\">Share</span></span></span></span></a></div>\n<div class=\"nc_tweetContainer swp_share_button swp_pinterest\" data-network=\"pinterest\"><a rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" class=\"nc_tweet swp_share_link noPop\" href=\"https://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smartmouth.com%2Ffaqs%2Fwhat-is-dry-mouth%2F\" onclick=\"event.preventDefault(); \n\t\t\t\