        "accordion_item_XN8y6d": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Can dry mouth cause cavities?",
            "content": "Dry mouth or xerostomia is a dryness in the mouth, often associated with a change or reduction in salivary flow. The saliva in our mouth helps to wash away food debris and reduce plaque. When dry mouth occurs it can cause cavities and tooth decay. That’s why it’s always helpful to rinse with SmartMouth Dry Mouth twice a day."
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_6WLffm": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Can dry mouth be cured?",
            "content": "The symptoms of dry mouth can be reduced, if not eliminated, by rinsing with SmartMouth Dry Mouth Oral Rinse twice a day."
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_yMpC8z": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How to prevent dry mouth while sleeping?",
            "content": "Saliva is important to maintain the health of your teeth and mouth. If you frequently have a dry mouth when you sleep or when you wake up in the morning, try rinsing with SmartMouth Dry Mouth or chew SmartMouth Dry Mouth Relief Mints."
          }
        }
      },
